Workers affiliated to the South African Municipal Workers’ Union, are protesting over wages, since Monday. Courtesy #DStv403 PRETORIA - The stench across the capital's CBD is getting worse. Workers affiliated to Samwu are escalating their wage increase protests. They're demanding an 18 percent pay hike in line with senior city officials. Garbage was strewn across the city and several intersections remain blocked. READ: Traffic chaos in Tshwane as bus drivers' strike enters day two Metro Police are calling for help saying are overstretched, but will help where they can. Tshwane Metro Police spokesperson Isaac Mahamba said some of their members are affiliated to Samwu. "We are saying now we are relying more on other law enforcement agencies," said Mahamba.